API.ADK

Class API_ADK.Device.MessageChannel

  • java.lang.Object
    • API.ADK.API_ADK.Device.MessageChannel
  • Enclosing class:
    API_ADK.Device

    public class API_ADK.Device.MessageChannel
extends java.lang.Object
    Subclass MessageChannel. This class is used for receiving and filtering message. It can only be used if the Controller object has been created. initializeMessageChannel(), deinitializeMessageChannel(), clearReceiveFilter(byte), addReceiveFilter(byte, int, byte), removeReceiveFilter(byte, int, byte), and setReceiveFilter(byte, boolean) can not be used if the controller is started. It could produce an error if the controller is receiving message while the message channel and filter configuration are changed.
    Author:
    hroesdiyono

        public ReturnCode addReceiveFilter(byte frameFormat,
                          int messageID,
                          byte frameType)
        Add an ID to the receive filter of active filter.
        Parameters:

        messageID - Input: The value of message ID (0 - 0x7FF for Standard frame and 0 - 0x1FFFFFFFF for Extended frame).
